  "text": "Although generally assumed to be an innocent electrocardiographic phenomenon, cardiac memory has also been hypothesized to be a marker of evolving pathology. [CITATION_1] 13 Moreover, one of the ion channel changes of cardiac memory is a transcriptionally induced reduction of potassium (I Kr ) channels.",
